<article>
    <h1>LIT&#xAD;TLE MISS MAN&#xAD;I&#xAD;CURES AT THE NAIL SO&#xAD;CIAL</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201225/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-25"><time>2020-12-25</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE STYLE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Mani- and pedi­cures for chil­dren can be a tad con­tro­ver­sial given the tox­i­c­ity of nail pol­ish, but moth­ers who want to give their lit­tle princesses a treat can rest easy at The Nail So­cial.</p>
    <p>The so­cially con­scious nail sa­lon uses mostly non-toxic, or­ganic, fair-trade prod­ucts – specif­i­cally the brands Zoya and Coat for its nail lac­quers, and An­gelPro and Jacqueline Burchell gel pol­ishes.</p>
    <p>The pol­ishes are free from formalde­hyde, cam­phor and other nasty chem­i­cals, mak­ing them safe for use on chil­dren and ex­pec­tant moth­ers.</p>
    <p>The sa­lon was es­tab­lished with the aim of pro­vid­ing lo­cal un­der­priv­i­leged women with train­ing and em­ploy­ment to im­prove their so­cial mo­bil­ity, so there is ed­u­ca­tional value to tak­ing your lit­tle ones here.</p>
    <p>A Lit­tle Miss man­i­cure and pedi­cure for girls aged 12 and be­low is priced at $10 each for a Quickie ex­press ser­vice, and $18 (man­i­cure) and $24 (pedi­cure) for the Sig­na­ture ser­vice.</p>
    <p>Of course, mum can get in on the pam­per­ing too. The Luxe treat­ment ($70 for man­i­cure and $80 for pedi­cure, or $140 for both) gets you the full works – nail shap­ing, cu­ti­cle care, sea salt ex­fo­li­a­tion, or­ganic clay masque and a co­conut oil mas­sage, fin­ished with a fresh coat of pol­ish.</p>
    <p>Nail art re­quests must be booked in ad­vance and prices vary with the de­sign. As part of the sa­lon’s Covid-19 safety and hy­giene mea­sures, cus­tomers are re­quired to bring their own ba­sic man­i­cure tools or pur­chase a kit in-store for $6.</p>
    <p>Info: 42A Haji Lane and 01-14, 333 Kreta Ayer Road. To book, call 6717-3221 (Haji Lane) or 6902-6753 (Kreta Ayer Road).</p>

